description:
The Explorers (The Epic of Flight)
Time Life Books | 1983 | ISBN: 0809433664 | PDF | 184 pages | 20.9 MB


The Explorers tells the story of man's aerial conquest of the last earthly frontiers: the North and South Poles, the Great Circle Route to Europe, the highest mountains, the deepest reaches of the South American and African jungles. The conquerors (and would-be...) of the Arctic and Antarctic will be familiar: Byrd, Peary, Amundsen, Nobile; less so the intrepid souls who opened the interior of darker continents
